ie.notes: From Internet Explorer 5.5 through 8, all elements of the array will not be deleted if deleteCount is omitted. This behavior was fixed in Internet Explorer 9.

nodejs.notes: Prior to Node.js 13.0.0, only the locale data for en-us is available by default. When other English locales are specified, the function silently falls back to en-us. When other languages are specified, it throws a RangeError. In order to make full ICU (locale) data available for versions prior to 13, see docs on the --with-full-icu= flag and how to provide the data.

firefox.notes: Starting in Firefox 74, toSource() is no longer available for use by web content. It is still allowed for internal and privileged code.
